<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/emailsecuritymatters" target=_blank><img  src="/images/contenu_en/socialmediaicons/rss_feed_30px.png" alt="Email Security Matters Blog RSS Feed" width=30 height=30/></a></p>

	<!-- Email Security Matters blog -->
	<a href="http://www.emailsecuritymatters.com" target="_blank"><h3 style="font-size: 18px;margin-top:10px;">Email Security Blog</h3></a>
	
	<ul>
	
	<li><a href="http://www.emailsecuritymatters.com/site/blog/category/what-is-the-best-way-to-communicate-with-support/" target="_blank" title="With the advent in the last decade of different technologies (Social Networking, Tweets, Blogs…), it seems that clients are less inclined to pick up the phone and call to explain their issues to the support teams and get a more personalized service.">What is the best way to communicate with Support?</a> (2012-03-30T16:54:25+00:00 by Patrick Yelle)</li>
	
	<li><a href="http://www.emailsecuritymatters.com/site/blog/category/fake-order-scams-jump-to-the-next-level/" target="_blank" title="Fake order confirmations are now a part of Spam Quarantine on a daily basis. But look at the latest edition of this Intuit Software Order confirmation (yes, it’s that time of year). If you’re an “instant panic” person, you might spot the first phone number and call to ask about this message, or simply express your frustration about the company.">Fake order scams jump to the next level</a> (2012-03-28T14:56:09+00:00 by Marc Chouinard)</li>
	
	<li><a href="http://www.emailsecuritymatters.com/site/blog/category/dns-blacklist-filtering-still-rules-but-for-how-long/" target="_blank" title="I came across a blog post from Virus Bulletin today, explaining that anti-spam solutions “displayed significantly lower spam catch rates [in their latest test] than in other recent tests.”  To explain this drop, Virus Bulletin hypothesized that “spammers are doing a better job at avoiding blacklists.”">DNS Blacklist filtering still rules, but for how long?</a> (2012-03-21T13:36:00+00:00 by Nicolas Riousset)</li>
	
	<li><a href="http://www.emailsecuritymatters.com/site/blog/category/local-tv-newscast-affected-by-malware-are-you-vulnerable-too/" target="_blank" title="On Twitter this morning I got a direct message from a local News Director, but it was a bit too friendly : "LOL... I'm laughing so hard at this pic of me someone uploaded"">Local TV newscast affected by malware: Are you vulnerable too?</a> (2012-03-13T18:34:36+00:00 by Marc Chouinard)</li>
	
	<li><a href="http://www.emailsecuritymatters.com/site/blog/category/spring-into-a-healthier-work-environment/" target="_blank" title="Where to start?  For your physical health, start with the biggest things:  (1) Look at your overall space first. You have to know how much room you have to fit in the improvements you need before you start thinking about what you want. (2) Ensure you have the budget/approval for the project and qualified people to help you make the changes.">Spring into a healthier work environment</a> (2012-03-12T14:06:18+00:00 by Jennifer Ansell)</li>
	
	</ul>
	  

